President Obama expressed his sadness at the passing of Prime Minister Meles Zenawi of Ethiopia. He recognized Meles's lifelong contribution to Ethiopia's development, especially his dedication to helping the country's poor. The President admired Meles's efforts to lift millions of Ethiopians out of poverty through his focus on food security. He also appreciated Meles's service for peace and security in Africa, his contributions to the African Union, and his representation of Africa on the global stage. The President offered his condolences to Meles's family and the people of Ethiopia, emphasizing the US government's commitment to its partnership with Ethiopia. Furthermore, he urged the Ethiopian government to strengthen its support for development, democracy, regional stability and security, human rights, and the well-being of its citizens.